### Basic Case Statements

Currently running through a sprint to learn the intermediate/advanced SQL concepts. 

Expression: CASE
Clauses: WHEN, THEN, ELSE, END

# Examples

```
CASE WHEN x = 1 THEN 'a'
     WHEN x = 2 THEN 'b'
     ELSE 'c' END AS new_column

or

```
CASE WHEN x = 1 THEN 'a'
     WHEN x = 2 THEN 'b'
     ELSE 'c' 
END AS new_column

# Full Syntax Example

```
SELECT
    column_1
    column_2
    column_3
CASE WHEN varible_1 > varible_2 THEN 'Output_1'
     WHEN varible_1 < varible_2 THEN 'Output_2'
     ELSE 'Output_3'
END AS outcome
FROM table
WHERE varible_4 = 'select_fields';

